According to a report from the State House, the ship manufacturing and marine services company, owned by an indigene of Akwa Ibom State, Charles Udonwa, has boosted the Governor’s vision of exploring and harnessing the maritime sector.  “We are here to stay. Other multinational companies are also going to establish along the same stretch. But we need the government to help us subdue militancy so that development would come.   To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .